text.tspan: Cumulative confirmed COVID-19 cases per million vs. GDP per capita, Dec
The color indicates the share of total cumulative tests that were positive. A high positive rate means testing is limited relative to
the scale of the outbreak and that the total number of cases of COVID-19 may be much higher than the number of confirmed
cases. Comparisons across countries are affected by differences in testing policies and reporting methods.
GDP per capita is adjusted for price differences between countries (it is expressed in international dollars).
